snippet.textDisplay: The very reason why reaction videos have become popular in Youtube is because of the reactions the audience see in the hosts' faces and changes in the pitch of their voices. Then comes the opinions of the hosts. This creates an environment where the audience feels like taking a journey with the hosts in their unboxing experience. With all these removed, I feel like I'm no longer involved in the process. This new POV format is just like googling pics of the product, the only differences is the pov feels creepier. I think why it feels creepy is because audiences have been programmed in the set up of thriller scenes, where they use silence to build up the jumpscare in movies.
